a^2 = 7 d^2
\frac{b}{a} = \frac{\sqrt{2}d}{\sqrt{7}d}=\sqrt{\frac{2}{7}}
\begin{eqnarray*} |AP|\cdot|AO| &=& |AA^\prime|\cdot|AB^\prime|\\ \implies (2-a)\cdot a &=& 2 d^2 \\ \implies (2-d\sqrt{7})\cdot d\sqrt{7} &=& 2 d^2 \\ \implies \frac{2\sqrt{7}}{9} &=& d \end{eqnarray*}
